1 remain at home;
2 (B) makes provisions for the child to contact the parent or guardian; and
3 (C) makes provisions for any reasonably foreseeable emergency.
4 (2) Except as provided in 16-6-305, a parent or guardian or any person who is 18 years of age or
5 older, whether or not the parent, guardian, or other person is supervising the welfare of the child, commits the
6 offense of endangering the welfare of children if the parent, guardian, or other person knowingly contributes to
7 the delinquency of a child less than:
8 (a) 18 years old by:
9 (i) supplying or encouraging the use of an intoxicating substance by the child;
10 (ii) causing or permitting the child to inhale, be exposed to, or ingest marijuana as defined in 50-
11 32-101, including products containing tetrahydrocannabinol (THC), including ingestible foods or drinks;or
12 (ii)(iii) assisting, promoting, or encouraging the child to enter a place of prostitution or human
13 trafficking as defined in 45-5-701;
14 (iv) assisting, promoting, or encouraging the child to enter an adult-use dispensary as defined in
15 16-12-102; or
16 (v) assisting, promoting, or encouraging the child to enter a place where the criminal production or
17 manufacture of dangerous drugs is taking place as described in 45-9-110; or
18 (b) 16 years old by assisting, promoting, or encouraging the child to:
19 (i) abandon the child's place of residence without the consent of the child's parents or guardian; or
20 (ii) engage in sexual conduct.
21 (3) A person, whether or not the person is supervising the welfare of a child less than 18 years of
22 age, commits the offense of endangering the welfare of children if the person, in the residence of a child, in a
23 building, structure, conveyance, or outdoor location where a child might reasonably be expected to be present,
24 in a room offered to the public for overnight accommodation, or in any multiple-unit residential building,
25 knowingly:
26 (a) produces or manufactures methamphetamine or attempts to produce or manufacture
27 methamphetamine;
28 (b) possesses any material, compound, mixture, or preparation that contains any combination of
